---
import ArticleLayout from '@/layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
---
<ArticleLayout
  title="BBQ It Mistakes to Avoid — Common Player Errors"
  description="Top mistakes new and intermediate BBQ It players make. Avoid these errors to progress faster and earn more money."
  quickAnswer="The most common mistakes are: burning meat, skipping perfect cooks, buying wrong upgrades first, not using offline grills, and ignoring customer offer quality."
  faq={[
    { question: 'What is the biggest mistake in BBQ It?', answer: 'Burning meat is the costliest mistake. A burnt meat sells for less than the raw cost, meaning you lose money on every burn. Remove meat early if unsure about timing.' },
    { question: 'Should I buy the most expensive grill first?', answer: 'No. Multiple cheaper upgrades compound faster than one expensive purchase. Buy the Standard Grill and Metal Table before saving for expensive endgame grills.' },
    { question: 'Is it bad to use low-tier meats?', answer: 'Not always. Low-tier meats like Hot Dogs are great for learning timing. But don\'t stay on them too long — switch to higher-tier meats as soon as your equipment supports it.' },
  ]}
  relatedGuides={[
    { title: 'Beginner Guide', url: '/beginner-guide/', description: 'Getting started right.' },
    { title: 'What to Buy First', url: '/what-to-buy-first/', description: 'Avoid bad purchase decisions.' },
    { title: 'Perfect Cook Guide', url: '/perfect-cook/', description: 'Stop burning meat.' },
  ]}
>
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Top 10 Mistakes</h2>
  <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-red-500 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">1. Burning Meat</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Burnt meat loses money. If unsure about timing, remove early (raw sells for more than burnt). Practice with cheap meats first.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-red-500 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">2. Skipping Perfect Cooks</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Normal cooks earn 50-75% less than perfect. The timing takes practice but the profit difference is enormous over hundreds of cooks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-orange-500 bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">3. Buying Expensive Upgrades Too Early</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Don't save 15,000 for BBQ Legend when you could buy Quick Hands + Seasoned Chef + Auto Sell for the same price. Multiple small upgrades compound faster.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-orange-500 bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">4. Not Using Offline Grills</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Offline grills earn money while you sleep. Not buying them means leaving free money on the table every day.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">5. Ignoring Customer Offers</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Accepting every offer without checking means sometimes selling below average value. Watch your offers, or get Auto Sell with a good table.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">6. Using Wrong Meat for Your Stage</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Cooking Dragon Ribs with a Basic Grill is a waste. Use the right meat for your equipment — check our <a href="/best-meat/" class="text-orange-500 underline">Best Meat guide</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">7. Mixing Meat Types on Grills</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Different meats have different cook times. Mixing makes perfect cooking much harder. Stick to one meat type across all active grills.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">8. Forgetting to Collect Offline Earnings</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Offline earnings cap out. Log in regularly to collect and reset the timer. Missing a cap means wasted passive income.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-gray-400 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">9. Not Using Codes</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Free cash from codes gives a huge early boost. Check our <a href="/codes/" class="text-orange-500 underline">Codes page</a> regularly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 border-l-4 border-gray-400 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-r-lg">
      <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">10. Poor Grill Placement</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Placing grills far from tables wastes time walking back and forth. Cluster everything together for maximum efficiency.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</ArticleLayout>
